For each customer, the simplified e-commerce schema stores the customer’s core profile in **`CUSTOMER_MASTER`**.

`CUSTOMER_MASTER` stores:
**`CUST_ID`** (INT, NOT NULL): unique customer identifier;  
**`FULL_NAME`** (VARCHAR(200), NOT NULL): customer’s full name;  
**`EMAIL`** (VARCHAR(150), NOT NULL, unique): email address for login;  
**`REGION_CODE`** (VARCHAR(10), NULL): geographic region used for tax calculation;  
**`CREATED_AT`** (DATETIME, NOT NULL): account creation timestamp;  
**`IS_ACTIVE`** (BOOLEAN, NOT NULL): whether the customer can place orders.

The business glossary also states a customer can have one or more delivery/billing addresses, but it notes that **customer addresses are “not in simplified schema”**, so address details are not stored in the simplified tables shown here.
